The administration and management of the area covered by the reservation shall be jointly under the Department of Environment and Natural Resources and Education, Culture and Sports. For this purpose, a five (5) year development plan shall be submitted to the Office of the President by the Board of Trustees of the Ifugao State College of Agriculture and Forestry within one (1) year from the approval hereof, furnishing the Department of Environment and Natural Resources and the Forest Management Bureau copies hereof.

The extraction and utilization of timber and other forest products remaining in the areas shall be subject to the Forest and Internal Revenue Laws and Regulations and to such other regulations that may hereafter be prescribed/promulgated.

In the event that the areas are no longer needed for the purpose stated, or their development has already been abandoned for a period of two (2) or more years, this Proclamation is automatically withdrawn, revoked or cancelled and the subject areas regain their original status as parts and parcels of the public/forest lands.

IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto set my hand and caused the seal of the Republic of the Philippines to be affixed.

Done in the City of Manila, this 19th day of February, in the year of Our Lord, nineteen hundred and ninety-two.

(Sgd.) CORAZON C. AQUINO

By the President: (Sgd.) FRANKLIN M. DRILON Executive Secretary

